  INCIDENT-CHANGELOG ANALYSIS
  ===========================
  
  Incident: IR-2024-0042 (Critical - Database breach via compromised service account)
  Date of Incident: 2024-11-14
  
  CHANGELOG RELEASES ANALYZED:
  - v0.1.0 (2024-01-10): Initial release, GET /api/users, in-memory storage
  - v0.2.0 (2024-02-15): POST /api/users endpoint, User case class
  - v0.3.0 (2024-03-10): Health check endpoint, email validation fix
  
  ANALYSIS:
  =========
  There is NO DIRECT RELATIONSHIP between the changelog releases and the incident.
  
  The incident (IR-2024-0042) was caused by:
  1. A service account password ('svc-analytics') being accidentally committed to a 
     public GitHub repository (example-corp/data-pipeline) on 2024-10-28
  2. The repository being made public during a team reorganization
  3. An attacker discovering the exposed credential 17 days later and using it to 
     access the production database
  
  The changelog only covers application-level changes:
  - API endpoints (GET/POST /api/users)
  - User data models
  - Health checks
  - Bug fixes (email validation)
  
  These are unrelated to:
  - Infrastructure and credential management
  - Service account configurations
  - GitHub repository security
   security
  
  CONCLUSION- CI/CD pipeline:
  ===========
  The incident was an infrastructure/security failure involving credential exposure 
  in a separate GitHub repository, NOT a webapp code issue. The webapp changelog 
  does not contain any releases related to this incident.
  
  The webapp versions (v0.1.0 - v0.3.0) predate the incident by months and contain 
  no changes that would have contributed to or prevented this type of security breach.
  
